wikipedia_page.main: Wyndham C. Emery (birth registered first ¼ 1897 – 1969) was a Welsh professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1920s. He played at representative level for Wales (Heritage № 78), and Other Nationalities, and at club level for Leigh (Heritage №), as a centre, i.e. number 3 or 4.
